## Fraud review object generalised: Withdrawal → Transaction (slice 4 follow-up)

### Context
Before merging slice 4, the core fraud-review object was generalised from
`Withdrawal` to `Transaction`. Rationale: moneypool's source data is a general
transactions ledger, the fraud signals (amount, velocity, device, geo) are
transaction-level, and future fraud surfaces (transfers, card payments) extend
by data instead of an ontology re-model. Withdrawals remain the first reviewed
type, distinguished by `txn_type`/`direction` columns on the source table.
Pure rename — no behavioral change; same suite results as slice 4.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/actions/types/review_transaction.py` (renamed from
   `review_withdrawal.py`) — `ReviewTransaction`/`ReviewTransactionParams`,
   `id="review_transaction"`, `object_type="Transaction"`, param
   `transaction_id`. Decision overlay value shape unchanged.
2. `src/back/core/graphql/ResolverFactory.py` — `make_review_transaction_resolver`,
   inner resolver/mutation field `reviewTransaction(transactionId, ...)`.
3. `src/back/core/graphql/GraphQLSchemaBuilder.py` — Mutation field renamed
   `reviewWithdrawal` → `reviewTransaction`.
4. `src/agents/tools/actions.py` — agent MCP tool `propose_review_transaction`.
5. `scripts/seed_fraud_transactions.sql` (renamed from
   `seed_fraud_withdrawals.sql`) — table `fraud_transactions`; added
   `txn_type` + `direction` columns; ids T1001–T1003.
6. Tests renamed/re-pointed: `test_review_transaction.py`,
   `test_review_transaction_mutation.py`, `test_transaction_overlay_field.py`
   (+ transaction naming in the override/SoD/agent-tool/integration tests).
7. Docs: `docs/architecture.md` (fraud loop now describes the general
   `Transaction` object + withdrawals-first note), `README.md`,
   `docs/sphinx/api/app.objects.actions.rst` (autodoc target), and an
   update note at the top of the slice-4 design spec.

